# Tauri dev watcher exclusions.
#
# Why this file exists:
# `tauri dev` walks every workspace crate that the app transitively
# depends on and watches each crate dir for changes. Two of those
# crates — provider-claude-sdk and provider-github-copilot — have a
# `bridge/` subdir with its own JS toolchain (pnpm + tsc). Their
# `build.rs` runs `pnpm install` and `pnpm run build` on (re)build, and
# pnpm rewrites `bridge/node_modules/.package-lock.json` as part of its
# internal bookkeeping — even on a no-op install.
#
# Without this ignore file, the sequence is:
#   1. cargo build → build.rs → pnpm touches node_modules/.package-lock.json
#   2. tauri watcher sees the write → triggers rebuild
#   3. goto 1 (infinite loop, the build never settles)
#
# Patterns are gitignore-style, matched against paths inside every
# watched crate dir.

# JS bridge artifacts in the provider crates. Patterns are gitignore-
# style and matched relative to each watched crate root, so both rooted
# and globbed forms are listed for safety across tauri-cli versions.
node_modules
node_modules/
**/node_modules
**/node_modules/**
bridge/node_modules
bridge/node_modules/**
bridge/dist
bridge/dist/**
**/.package-lock.json
**/.pnpm-install-stamp
